quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  83,7,"But no, indeed the record{1}of the wicked is in Sijjeen{2}.",footnotes:1:[Literally ‘scripture’.],footnotes:2:[<i>Sijjeen</i> is derived from the word ‘<i>sijn</i>’ which means ‘prison’. Here, Allah is expressing the gravity of the matter and describing it as an eternal prison and a painful torment.]
  83,8,"And what can make you<sup>sg </sup>realize what Sijjeen is?"
  83,9,"A written record<sup>d </sup>."
  83,10,"Woe on that day to the disbelievers"
